description.displayText: Jaclyn is a super Nanny! We have had the pleasure of her caring for our son C. (9) & daughter N. (4) for the last 4 years. Unfortunately, me & family are moving out of state this summer. Jaclyn picks up & drops off my children from my house in Brooklyn & takes them back to her house where she watches them and her two lovely daughters. I knew when I met Jaclyn I'd hit the jackpot between her credentials & upbeat attitude, I am very lucky to have met her & have my children around her for the last 3 years. Jaclyn is a safe driver of a newer Chevrolet traverse that is spotless & her house is set up perfectly for children with tons of toys, activities, & safety precautions. I never worried about my children going hungry or not having nutritious meals in her care. Jaclyn is an efficient multitasker, she would help my son C. with his homework while simultaneously taking care of the other children & everyone was always happy. Any family will be lucky to have her in their lives!

description.displayText: Jaclyn is not just a nanny/babysitter but has become part of our family. We hired her two years ago and since then she's proven to be someone we can truly count on and trust. She's knowledgeable about childhood growth and development and partners with you on nurturing your children. My boys are 3.5 years old and 15 months...they love her! We still count on her. Happy to be a reference anytime.

description.displayText: Jaclyn is an amazing young lady.  I worked with her in an academy for many years. Jaclyn was the teacher assistant for my 4 year old daughter. Jaclyn pours all her love and experience into her job.  All staff and parents love her. Jaclyn is easy to get along, always willing to help in any situation and is trustworthy. Jaclyn will be an asset to any employer that she works for.

description.displayText: Jaclyn was a wonderful responsible young lady. She was fabulous with my boys she helped them with there homework made sure they read but most of all she played with them. My boys absolutely love her till this day she is still in there life. I wish I still was able to use her but I'm a study at home Mom now. She gave me peace of mind that my boys where safe and happy.
